content:
The Response Action ends an Integration Procedure and returns data to the entity that called it. It can also add data to the data JSON or end conditionally. Response Actions are useful for debugging Integration Procedures. They are also useful for trimming the data response. For specific trimming strategies, see Manipulate JSON with the Send/Response Transformations Properties.

For Integration Procedure examples that include at least one Response Action, see Process Arrays Using Loop Blocks, Handle Errors Using Try-Catch Blocks, and Integration Procedure Action for Integration Procedures.
title: Response Action for Integration Procedures
